edu.harvard.data.identity

Class IdentityScrubber<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.Mapper<Object,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,org.apache.hadoop.io.NullWritable>
      • edu.harvard.data.identity.IdentityScrubber<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the dataset's main identifier.

    public abstract class IdentityScrubber<T>
extends org.apache.hadoop.mapreduce.Mapper<Object,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,org.apache.hadoop.io.Text,org.apache.hadoop.io.NullWritable>
    Base class for the identity scrub mapper job. As the second part of the identity phase, an instance of this map job is run for every identifying table in the data set. It is recommended but not required that these subclasses be generated; see IdentityScrubberGenerator for code that generates the subclasses.

    There is no corresponding reduce step for this map job; the output of the mapper is written directly as the output of the identity phase.

    The class contains a setup method that reads an existing identity map from the Hadoop distributed cache to create an Map from the main identifier type (type parameter T) to IdentityMap. It also contains a map method that uses the subtype's populateRecord(org.apache.commons.csv.CSVRecord) method to copy all non-identifier fields from the previous phase's version of the record.

      • populateRecord

        protected abstract DataTable populateRecord(org.apache.commons.csv.CSVRecord csvRecord)
        Parse a CSVRecord object to create an instance of the DataTable type that represents this table.
        Parameters:
        csvRecord - the data to be populated in the new object.
        Returns:
        a parsed object containing the data from the csvRecord parameter. This DataTable object should represent the state of the record at the end of the previous phase (e.g. if the identity phase is running as Phase 1 of the data pipeline, the returned value should be of the correct type to represent the output of Phase 0).
